      'Teach statistical analysis and visual data literacy.',
      'Encourage pattern recognition and error detection.',
      'Use global demographic data to teach critical inquiry and intercultural understanding.',
      'How RealLives Was Used:',
      'Students explored simulated lives across countries and collected real-world life data from the simulation.',
      'They created graphs and tables based on health, education, income, and demographic trends.',
      'The class held discussions on root causes of social problems and proposed solutions.',
      'Students wrote letters to the United Nations, merging data interpretation with civic voice.',
      'This is mathematics as cultural insight, as empathy, and as social responsibility. It shows how RealLives can support competency development, student agency, and teacher well-being - all in a traditionally content-driven subject.',
      'Conclusion: Teaching with Heart, Head, and Horizon',
